theorem clopen_of_closed_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hClosed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP3 : Topology.P3 (A : Set X)) :
    IsClopen (A : Set X) := by
  have hOpen : IsOpen (A : Set X) :=
    (Topology.isOpen_of_closed_P3 (A := A) hClosed hP3)
  exact ⟨hOpen, hClosed⟩

theorem clopen_of_closed_P2 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hClosed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP2 : Topology.P2 A) :
    IsClopen (A : Set X) := by
  -- First, obtain that `A` is open from `P2` and its closedness.
  have hOpen : IsOpen (A : Set X) :=
    isOpen_of_closed_P2 (A := A) hClosed hP2
  -- Combine openness and closedness into the `IsClopen` structure.
  exact ⟨hOpen, hClosed⟩

theorem clopen_of_closed_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hClosed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP3 : Topology.P3 (A : Set X)) :
    IsClopen (A : Set X) := by
  exact ⟨isOpen_of_closed_P3 (A := A) hClosed hP3, hClosed⟩

theorem clopen_of_closed_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hClosed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP3 : Topology.P3 A) :
    IsClopen (A : Set X) := by
  -- From `P3` and the closedness of `A`, we deduce that `A` is open.
  have hOpen : IsOpen (A : Set X) :=
    (Topology.P3_closed_iff_open (A := A) hClosed).1 hP3
  -- Combine the closedness and openness to obtain that `A` is clopen.
  exact ⟨hClosed, hOpen⟩
